Four Charged After Ferry Sinks Off Zanzibar, The Citizen Reports

-- B y   D a v i d   M a l i n g h a   D o y a
-- 
2011-09-17T07:08:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-17/four-charged-after-ferry-sinks-off-zanzibar-the-citizen-reports.html
     Sept. 17 (Bloomberg News) -- Four people were charged with
“causing death” after more than 200 people died when a ferry
sailing off  Tanzania ’s coast sunk on Sept. 9, The Citizen said,
citing Ramadhan Nasib, the director of public prosecution.  The charged are expected to appear in court on Sept. 19,
the Dar es Salaam-based newspaper reported.  The MV Spice Islander sank at about midnight on Sept. 9
while en route to Pemba Island, 50 kilometers (31 miles) north
of Zanzibar’s main island of Unguja.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  